## Summary checklist (HandsOff)

- [ ] Test cases: written to `test_cases/<Topic_name>.md` (single file with Backend/Frontend split); .md file verified on disk; test_cases/README.md updated.
- [ ] **Precondition completeness:** Every TC has a full data chain (Customer → POD → Product → Contract → Billing run → Invoice → Payment etc.); specific where the test demands it, generic where any instance works; dates and amounts included when they affect the outcome.
- [ ] Playwright: spec created in `EnergoTS/tests/cursor/{JIRA_KEY}-*.spec.ts` (or equivalent); file verified on disk; **number of `test()` blocks equals total number of test cases (TC-BE-N + TC-FE-N) in the .md file** – full coverage, 1:1.
- [ ] **Validation (Step 4.5):** playwright-test-validator invoked; if failed, re-run test-case-generator and/or energo-ts-test and re-validate until pass or max iterations; only then run tests.
- [ ] Report: content is **only** Playwright test results (per test: what is verified, steps, result, failure reason); if validation had issues, include a short Validation section.
- [ ] Slack: report built from **`Cursor-Project/config/template/Slack_report_template.md`**; full report sent **only** to **Tester** (DM) and **#ai-report** (channel_id **C0AK96S1D7X**); **never** to Assignee or anyone else; not a short summary.
- [ ] Agent questions: after report, collect questions from each participating agent (as needed); each question tagged with agent name; send questions after the report to the same recipients (Tester and #ai-report only).

Violation: repeat of the above problems is a workflow error; correct before considering HandsOff complete.
